trigger.name: Input OverPower Fault
trigger.description: Indicates whether the alarm of InputOverPowerFault exists in the power shelf. This alarm will occur when the input power of the power shelf exceeds the threshold continuously for the duration. And it will be cleared when the input power falls below the recovery threshold continuously for the duration. The thresholds and duration are user-configurable respectively.

item.name: Shelf Input OverPower Fault Clear Threshold
item.description: The recovery threshold of InputOverPowerFault (Watts).

item.name: Shelf Input OverPower Fault Occur Threshold
item.description: The occurrence threshold of InputOverPowerFault (Watts). When this value is zero, InputOverPowerFault will not occur.

item.name: Shelf Input OverPower Warnig Clear Threshold
item.description: The recovery threshold of InputOverPowerWarning (Watts).

item.name: Shelf Input OverPower Warnig Occur Threshold
item.description: The occurrence threshold of InputOverPowerWarning (Watts). When this value is zero, InputOverPowerWarning will not occur.

trigger.name: Shelf Input OverPower
trigger.description: Indicates whether the alarm of InputOverPowerWarning exists in the power shelf. This alarm will occur when the input power of the power shelf exceeds the threshold continuously for the duration. And it will be cleared when the input power falls below the recovery threshold continuously for the duration. The thresholds and duration are user-configurable respectively

item.name: Shelf Phase Power L1 to L2 or N
item.description: The three-phase input power between Line 1 and X (Watts). The measurement lines depend on the connection type as below. Delta :Line 1 to Line 2 Wye :Line 1 to Neutral

item.name: Shelf Total Input Power
item.description: The total input power of the power shelf (Watts). The measuring method of this value depends on the presence or absence of ATS. Any ATSes are NOT mounted :The sum of all PSUs' input power. One or two ATSes are mounted :The input power of the active ATS.
